closes ticket 94 It includes all the infrastructure to support the sensors that the research group brainstormed a couple weeks ago New tests are included to cover some of the code The research database is also upgraded to receive this information There is also a new python script to be the intermediary between this new sensor data and the sql database The new paradigm for sensor s that aren t implemented is for them to be null rather than some valid but nonsensical answer like 1 for network Load This commit also supports upgrading from old databases May it not break your build Location    </dd>\n          <dt class=\"property author\">Author:</dt>\n          <dd class=\"author\">djp3</dd>\n          <dt class=\"property message\">Message:</dt>\n          <dd class=\"message searchable\">\n            \n            \n              <p>\nThis commit closes <a class=\"closed ticket\" href=\"/LUCICodeRepository/nomaticIM/ticket/94\" title=\"defect: Build infrastructure to support upgraded sensor collection (closed: fixed)\">ticket:94</a>  It includes all the infrastructure to support the sensors that the research group brainstormed a couple weeks ago.  New tests are included to cover some of the code.   The research database is also upgraded to receive this information.  There is also a new python script to be the intermediary between this new sensor data and the sql database.  The new paradigm for sensor's that aren't implemented is for them to be null rather than some valid but nonsensical answer like -1.0 for network Load.  This commit also supports upgrading from old databases.  May it not break your build.<br />\n</p>\n\n            \n            \n          </dd>\n          <dt class=\"property location\">Location:</dt>\n          <dd class=\"searchable\"><a href=\"/LUCICodeRepository/nomaticIM/browser/nomatic/trunk/service/edu/uci/ics/luci/nomatic/service?rev=622\">nomatic/trunk/service/edu/uci/ics/luci/nomatic/service</a></dd>\n        <dt class=\"property files\">\n          Files:\n        </dt>\n        <dd class=\"files\">\n          <div class=\"legend\" id=\"file-legend\">\n            <dl>\n              <dt
